&lt;hr>
&lt;p>Since I began building websites in Y2K, I&amp;rsquo;ve lost count how many times the phrase &amp;ldquo;&amp;hellip;there&amp;rsquo;s got to be a better way to do this&amp;rdquo; has passed my lips. Most times, while fighting with floats and widths of content and sidebars or just basically trying to get something beside something else without using a stupid &lt;code>TABLE&lt;/code>.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Bakeoff</title><link>https://mhicks.me/research/bakeoff/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jul 2019 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://mhicks.me/research/bakeoff/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;img src="formspree-logo.png" alt="Formspree Logo">&lt;/p>




&lt;h2 id="formspree-makes-it-easy-to-receive-submissions-from-html-forms-on-your-static-website">
&lt;a href="https://formspree.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Formspree&lt;/a> makes it easy to receive submissions from HTML forms on your static website.
 &lt;a href="#formspree-makes-it-easy-to-receive-submissions-from-html-forms-on-your-static-website">&lt;svg class="anchor-symbol" aria-hidden="true" height="26" width="26" viewBox="0 0 22 22" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
